-- Russia Equity Movers: Norilsk Nickel, Lukoil, Alrosa Active
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 2012-03-01T16:48:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/russia-equity-movers-norilsk-nickel-lukoil-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock Micex index was little
changed, down less than 0.1 percent to 1,595.78 at the close in
Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS index fell 0.7 percent to
1,723.57.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH)  (LKOH RX) retreated 0.3 percent to 1,870.50
rubles. Russia’s second-biggest oil company said fourth-quarter
net income slumped 39 percent to $1.35 billion from $2.19
billion a year earlier, missing estimates.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN)  (GMKN RX) slid as much as 1.9
percent, the steepest drop since Feb. 22, and closed down 0.4
percent at 5,754 rubles. The world’s largest producer of
palladium declined as the metal for June delivery fell as much
as 1.3 percent to $702 per ounce in  New York .  OAO Alrosa (ALRS)  (ALRS RX) rose 2.4 percent to 32.857 rubles
after Alexei Uvarov, head of the  Economy Ministry ’s property
department, said the federal government and the Yakutia region
agreed to each sell 7 percent of  Russia ’s diamond mining
monopoly.  To contact the reporter on this story:
